Hey Calvin and Mark,

Thank you for taking the time to meet with us yesterday. To recap our meeting, we:


	Found a DLL error from our last HF patch on 1/30



	
	
		It looks like instructions to resolve this were sent out 1/31 but no response.
		We resolved this issue by unblocking all of the SharePoint DLLs in the PrivateAssemblies folder with the date of 01/30/2025 and then kicked off a new SPAC System Scan.
	
	



	Investigated the SP Bulk Import error (Foreign Key constraint) with development and found that the USN was much higher than the expected value. 



	
	
		A fix for this is expected from development some time next week.
	
	



Let me know how the SPAC System Scan looks when it finishes up, and I'll be in touch once I've received the patch from development (unless they have any other questions first).

Thank you,

Tay Caliguiri

At the end of our meeting, the bulk import was rolling along- let us know how this is looking tomorrow and we'll go from there!

Thank you,

TextBody:
Hey Team,

Thank you for meeting with us today. To recap our session, we reviewed the SPAA System Scan and Bulk Import and are no longer being held up by Bulk Import foreign key constraint issue! It looks like our upgrade to NEA v11.6.0.138 resolved that issue for us. We also took a peak at the SPAC System scan and spun off a new ticket to get the FileTranscriptContentEdited event type added to our sharepoint activity mappings (ticket #00440262).

Karolis will also reach out with some additional resources to get a full Netwrix Health Check commissioned.

I'll proceed with closing this ticket out, but please do not hesitate to reach out here and reopen the ticket if the bulk import error returns.

Following this email, you will receive an automated confirmation that the case is closed. Feel free to leave any feedback via the survey link!

Thank you,

Tay Caliguiri
